{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6b6623d6-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s702a–1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"702a–1"},"text":"§ 702a–1.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Modification of project of 1927; adoption","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The project for the control of floods of the Mississippi River and its tributaries, adopted by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s702a"},"text":"section 702a of this title","children":[],"tail":", is modified in accordance with the recommendations of section 43 of the report submitted by the Chief of Engineers to the Chairman of the Committee on Flood Control, dated "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1935-02-12"},"text":"February 12, 1935","children":[],"tail":", and printed in House Committee on Flood Control Document Numbered 1, Seventy-fourth Congress, first session, as, in sections 642a, 702a–2 to 702a–12, 702g–1, 702j–1, 702j–2, 702k–1, and 702k–2 of this title, further modified and amended; and as so modified is adopted and authorized and directed to be prosecuted under the direction of the Secretary of the Army and the supervision of the Chief of Engineers."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6b6623d7-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1936-06-15/ch548/s1"},"text":"June 15, 1936, ch. 548, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/1508"},"text":"49 Stat. 1508","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343"},"text":"July 26, 1947, ch. 343","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 205(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6b6623d8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6b6623d9-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id6b6623da-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 702a–1½, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-28/ch795/s4"},"text":"act June 28, 1938, ch. 795, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1220"},"text":"52 Stat. 1220","children":[],"tail":", which related to further modification of 1927 project, was transferred to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s702a–1a"},"text":"section 702a–1a of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 702a–1¾, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1941-08-18/ch377/s3"},"text":"act Aug. 18, 1941, ch. 377, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/55/642"},"text":"55 Stat. 642","children":[],"tail":", which related to further modificiation and adoption of Lower Mississippi River flood control project, was transferred to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s702a–1b"},"text":"section 702a–1b of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id6b6623db-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id6b6623dc-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Department of War designated Department of the Army and title of Secretary of War changed to Secretary of the Army by section 205(a) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-26/ch343/tII"},"text":"act July 26, 1947, ch. 343, title II","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/501"},"text":"61 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":". Section 205(a) of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1947","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by section 53 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/641"},"text":"70A Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":". Section 1 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1956-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956","children":[],"tail":", enacted “Title 10, Armed Forces” which in sections 3010 to 3013 continued Department of the Army under administrative supervision of Secretary of the Army."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
